Pitso Mosimane, coach of Mamelodi Sundowns with Patrice Motsepe, Chairman of Mamelodi Sundowns during the Absa Premiership 2019/20 Mamelodi Sundowns Press Conference at the ARM House, Johannesburg on the 21 May 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Mamelodi Sundowns president Patrice Motsepe has finally ended speculation surrounding the future of Pitso Mosimane. Having already spent eight years at Chloorkop, 'Jingles' has extended his contract by a further four-years. Among a whole host of trophies the 55-year-old has won with the Brazilians, he also led them to the 2016 Caf Champions League. READ: 'I have no shame, I benefitted': Mosimane Sundowns extended Mosimane's contract until the 2023/24 season. “One of the main reasons for me to renew my contract with Mamelodi Sundowns is the president’s trust and faith in me, he trusted me to lead this team to where it is – and fulfill his wish to build a team to conquer Africa. It’s humbling to be part of a brand like Sundowns and contribute to its success, especially as a local coach and also having played for the team,” Mosimane said.